TI  - A study of the association between fear of negative evaluation, aggressive behavior and mobile phone addiction among Chinese university students: a network analysis
PY  - 2026
JO  - CURRENT PSYCHOLOGY
DO  - 10.1007/s12144-026-09095-5
AB  - This study examined the fine-grained associations among aggressive behavior, mobile phone addiction, and fear of negative evaluation in a sample of Chinese university students. From March to June 2023, 4998 university students from Wuhan, China, were surveyed using the Aggressive Behavior Scale, the Mobile Phone Addiction Questionnaire, and the Fear of Negative Evaluation Scale. Network analysis in R 4.3.3 identified central and bridge nodes through network estimation, centrality, predictability, and stability assessments."Hostility" emerged as the most central node (EI = 4.87), followed by "Indirect Aggression" (EI = 4.55). "Fear of Negative Evaluation" and "Inefficiency" were the key bridge nodes (EI = 3.28 and 2.51, respectively). The average predictability across all nodes was 0.53. These findings suggest that targeting these nodes may inform early and targeted mental health interventions for university students.
